<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sill</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-20"><hi rend="italic">November 20,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Allen’s dispatches 156 and following received. Confine yourself strictly
                            protection of American citizens and interests. You have no concern in
                            internal affairs. Your actions to be taken independently of other
                            representatives unless otherwise instructed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>